<subSubSection id="2EFC6504893BEF22FF41D5BCADD0FBE7" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="6659368F893BEF22FF41D5BCADD0FBE7" blockId="7.[192,1440,930,1082]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="5492EA9D893BEF22FF41D5BCAE53FC67" bold="true" box="[192,324,930,954]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Remarks:</emphasis>
This is a common flea of the meadow vole, 
<taxonomicName id="A1E64D0C893BEF22FCE2D5BCAB5EFC67" baseAuthorityName="Ord" baseAuthorityYear="1815" box="[867,1097,930,954]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Microtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pennsylvanicus">
<emphasis id="5492EA9D893BEF22FCE2D5BCAB5EFC67" box="[867,1097,930,954]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">M. pennsylvanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in eastern North America. Although this flea has been reported from 
<taxonomicName id="A1E64D0C893BEF22FD47D5DCAC6DFC07" baseAuthorityName="Wagner" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[710,890,962,986]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Microtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ochrogaster">
<emphasis id="5492EA9D893BEF22FD47D5DCAC6DFC07" box="[710,890,962,986]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">M. ochrogaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingRegion id="A422F86D893BEF22FC20D5DCACE0FC07" box="[929,1015,962,986]" country="United States of America" name="Illinois" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Illinois</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="02774B7E893BEF22FB87D5DCAB9AFC07" author="Verts, B. J." box="[1030,1165,962,986]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" pagination="471 - 476" refId="ref11259" refString="Verts, B. J. 1961. Observations on the fleas (Siphonaptera) of some small mammals in northwestern Illinois. American Midland Naturalist 66: 471 - 476." type="journal article" year="1961">Verts 1961</bibRefCitation>
), this is not a common association, so these are important new records. 
<bibRefCitation id="02774B7E893BEF22FD7ED5FCACB0FC27" author="Wilson, N." box="[767,935,994,1018]" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" refId="ref11515" refString="Wilson, N. 1961. The Ectoparasites (Ixodides, Anoplura, and Siphonaptera) of Indiana Mammals. PhD thesis. Purdue University. 525 p." type="book" year="1961">Wilson (1961)</bibRefCitation>
, collecting from 
<taxonomicName id="A1E64D0C893BEF22FBE7D5FCAA53FC27" baseAuthorityName="Ord" baseAuthorityYear="1815" box="[1126,1348,994,1018]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Microtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pennsylvanicus">
<emphasis id="5492EA9D893BEF22FBE7D5FCAA53FC27" box="[1126,1348,994,1018]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">M. pennsylvanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, makes it clear that 
<taxonomicName id="A1E64D0C893BEF22FEDAD21CAEA3FBC4" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[347,436,1026,1049]" class="Aves" family="Strigidae" genus="Megascops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Strigiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="asio">
<emphasis id="5492EA9D893BEF22FEDAD21CAEA3FBC4" box="[347,436,1026,1049]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">M. asio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a nest flea, rarely found in high numbers on the body of the host. 
<taxonomicName id="A1E64D0C893BEF22FA86D21CAFE6FBE4" baseAuthorityName="Baker" baseAuthorityYear="1904" class="Insecta" family="Ceratophyllidae" genus="Megabothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonaptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asio">
<emphasis id="5492EA9D893BEF22FA86D21CAFE6FBE4" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">Megabothris asio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was the only flea collected from voles.
</paragraph>
